output:
This report all remote call inside a loop. 
It provides the following information:
 - Caller Artifact Full Name that contains the loop
 - path until the remote called artifact

Note that:
1/ The call path may contains different path while only one is an error. For example:
g(){myException()}
 f() {
       while { g ()}
        g()
        } 

will report both path to g() while only one is a violation.

2/ 2/ Several paths for the same method violating the rule are identified in the Metric Detail page by a sequence ID (in the Value column), this ID is dynamically set during each snapshot and the same path can have a different sequence ID in different snapshots.
